{"title": "Revolution, and other Essays", "description": "A collection of 13 essays written between 1900 and 1908, published in 1910. The lead essay, \"Revolution\", outlines how and why London renounced capitalism as a failed social system and declared himself an active participant in the \"socialist revolution\", the last essay is an autobiographical piece, and the essays in between are on diverse subjects. A few of the \u201cessays\u201d are actually humorous short fiction stories; others are serious, sometimes angry rants against capitalistic greed and political corruption. All of the pieces are thought-provoking and excellently written, though only loosely intellectual, highly opinionated, and rife with contradiction, as was London himself. -- Summary by Michele Fry", "duration": 22045, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "143", "name": "Jack London"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/revolution_and_other_essays_1403_librivox/revolution_1403.jpg", "copyright_year": "1910", "genres": ["Essays & Short Works", "Political Science"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Michele Fry"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Crln Yldz Ksr"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Kathrine Engan"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Revolution", "readers": [8463], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/revolution_and_other_essays_1403_librivox/revolution_01_london_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2999}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Somnambulists", "readers": [8820], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/revolution_and_other_essays_1403_librivox/revolution_02_london_64kb.mp3", "duration": 942}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Dignity of Dollars", "readers": [8820], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/revolution_and_other_essays_1403_librivox/revolution_03_london_64kb.mp3", "duration": 978}, {"section": 4, "title": "Goliah, Part I", "readers": [8575], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download